cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and visual tracking, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The use of deep learning and attention mechanisms also suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel algorithm for training deep classifiers, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The use of attention maps for tracking also suggests that it could belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on large-scale benchmark datasets, which could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
